---
name: interpreter is javascript only
description: The gleam_interpreter has promises and can only run on the JavaScript runtime.
date: 2026-05-30
---

Earlier in development an experiment to support async work via promises was added to the interpreter.
In EYG everything should be explicit, so any program using async/await would reveal this through one of both of the Async/Await effect.
Because an Await effect needs to be implemented in the runtime the runtime is built on promises.
This means that the gleam_interpreter cannot run on erlang.

Currently the supported runtimes have effects for `Fetch` and `ReadFile` etc that are synchronous and do not require `Await`.

## Future direction

The promise value could be removed from the interpreter value representation.
This would be a breaking change but not effect anyone at this time.

Promise functionality could be recreated on the BEAM as a noop.

Another concurrency story could be the right approach for EYG and the interpreter could be left as is until that is clear.